<div>
  <h2> Simple batchload </h2>

  <div class="flexbox full_viewport_whitespace">
    <div class="item item1">
      <h3> Description and requirements </h3>

      <p> Creates asserted distributions (distribution records for taxa, not specimens, from published accounts).
        You must provide at least one of otu_name OR otu_id, if both provided otu_id will be used.
        You must provide at least one of country, state, county, if more than one provided all will be used to match and
        the finest recorded.
        You must provide at least one of source_id, doi, citation, if more than provided priority of use is source_id,
        doi, then citation.
        <em> A text file with unix line endings is required.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="item item2">
      <h3> Example file </h3>
      <table>

        <tr class="underlined_rows">
          <td colspan="2">one of these</td>
          <td colspan="4">this &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            OR one or more of these
          </td>
          <td colspan="3">one of these</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th>otu_name</th>
          <th>otu_id</th>
          <th>geographic_area_name</th>
          <th>country</th>
          <th>state</th>
          <th>county</th>
          <th>source_id</th>
          <th>doi</th>
          <th>citation</th>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <td>Aus bus</td>
          <td></td>
          <td></td>
          <td>Canada</td>
          <td>Saskatchewan</td>
          <td></td>
          <td>19</td>
          <td></td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td>19</td>
          <td>Alaska</td>
